    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-01-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="27"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2123.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-01-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 20, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir: R</hi>eferring to my No. 2097 in regard to the
                    question pending between the governments of Great Britain and Nicaragau,
                    concerning the Musquito territory, I now inclose for your information a copy of
                    a dispatch<note n="*" xml:id="d27fn1">For inclosure dispatch No. 144, December
                        23, 1867, from the United States minister to Nicaragua.</note> from the
                    United States minister to Nicaragua, containing the correspondence between Mr.
                    Dickinson and the minister for foreign affairs regarding the action which this
                    government has taken in the matter.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
